ENTRY            F1538   20251216   20260305   20260305       F106
SUBENT        F1538001   20251216   20260305   20260305       F106
BIB                 13         38
TITLE      Excitation functions and yields for 66,67,68Ga
           production via deuteron irradiation of natural zinc
AUTHOR     (G.Mehmonov,N.E.V.Pineda,A.A.Garapatsky,L.A.Hasnowo,
           S.Khujaev,S.Egamediev)
INSTITUTE  (4UZ UZB,4RUSTPI)
           (3INSINS) National Research and Innovation Agency,
           Yogyakarta, Indonesia
REFERENCE  (J,NET,57,103611,2025)
           #doi:10.1016/j.net.2025.103611
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4RUSTPI) U-120 Cyclotron
SAMPLE     The stack consisted of two different metal foils;
           natZn (99.9% purity), with isotopic composition of
           64Zn-(49.17%), 66Zn-(27.73%), 67Zn-(4.04%), 68Zn-
            (18.45%) and 70Zn-(0.61%) was used as the main
           target, and natCu foil (99.9% purity) composed of
           63Cu-(69.15%) and 65Cu-(30.85%) was used as monitor.
           Both zinc and copper foils were 10+-0.15 mu-m thick.
           Eleven sets of Cu-Zn-Cu foil sandwiches were stacked
           to form the target with an aluminum support
           containing a 10 mm aperture to collimate the deuteron
           beam and hold the foils in place.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) High-purity Canberra Ge detector (type GC1020,
           diameter 46.5 mm, length 32 mm, 10% relative efficiency
           and energy resolution of 2 keV for the 1.332 MeV
           gamma-line of the 60Co standard source) coupled with
           a multi-channel analyzer, was used.
METHOD     (STTA,GSPEC,EDEG)
           (ACTIV) The target was irradiated for 20 minutes with
           a current below 20 nA.
MONITOR   1(29-CU-65(D,2N)30-ZN-65,,SIG)
          2(29-CU-63(D,2N)30-ZN-63,,SIG)
DECAY-MON 1(30-ZN-65,243.93D,DG,1115.53,0.5004)
          2(30-ZN-63,38.47MIN,DG,669.62,0.082,
                              DG,962.06,0.065)
ADD-RES    (COMP) Comparison with data from the TENDL-2023 nuclear
           library.
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry was approved by Dr. G.Mehmonov.
HISTORY    (20251216C)
ENDBIB              38
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           41
